      "content": "i get that it's a mixed bag, but when you say it \"achieved its immediate objectives,\" isn't that a bit of a stretch? if the end result was a power vacuum and regional instability, doesn't that fundamentally negate any strategic success? it feels like calling it a success while acknowledging it caused a collapse is a bit contradictory. shouldn't the long-term stability of a region be a core part of the \"geopolitical standpoint\"?",
